				h1.articleheading HOW TO PLAY DEADEYE
				p.articletext Handguns. Shotguns. Sniper Rifles. Plastique. The no-nonsense mercenary Deadeye is happy is use whatever it takes to get the job done. Deadeye herself has no natural superpowers, but has frequently clashed with both heroes and villains in dangerous shootouts. If you've got the guts to take the safety off, playing as Deadeye offers explosive rewards. That is, if you are willing to pull the trigger.

				p.articletext Deadeye is an aggressive combo deck that can alternate between attacking your opponent's hand and their life total. Her AIM skill allows you to dramatically increase the damage dealt by cards in your deck. When playing as Deadeye, it's not uncommon to play Actions dealing upwards of 8 damage. Don't expect to have access to a lot of defensive options, but why bother? Sometimes it only takes one shot.
	
				p.articletext While playing Deadeye, you'll have to embrace being cutthroat. Deadeye offers a lot of options in terms of player damage and discard strategies, but struggles with surviving into the later turns of the game. Of course, players can include more defensive Crossovers as a way of shoring up this weakness. By regularly and aggressively attacking your opponent, Deadeye shines as one of the centerpiece aggressive characters of the game. Due to her status as an beginner-friendly combo character, Deadeye has been classified as an EASY character. Want to set the pace? Tired of waiting around for slow players? Pick up Deadeye and start firing live rounds.
