				h1.articleheading WHAT IS DEADEYE'S SKILL?
				p.articletext Trained to handle dangerous weapons from a young age, Deadeye has excellent combat reflexes and pinpoint accuracy. As an experienced war veteran, Deadeye is also happy to utilize surveillance devices and explosives to hunt her targets. Deadeye's special skill AIM represents her ability to maximize damage by hitting your opponent right where it counts.

				.row
					.col-md-12.text-center.articleskillpanel
						img(src="../../images/aim.png")
						h4.articleskilltext Cards in your deck give you Aim points. Whenever your Actions or Feats deal damage, add your Aim to that damage. At the end of each turn, reset your Aim to 0.

				p.articletext So how does Aim work? Your Aim score is a number that begins each turn at 0. By playing cards that increase your Aim score, you can give cards in your deck a temporary damage boost based on your Aim score. This allows you to power-up cards in your deck by waiting until you can take advantage of a big Aim bonus! Let's look at an example.

				.row
					.col-md-6.articlecardpanel
						img.articlevertimg.center-block(src='../../images/de/emptyclip.png')
						h4.articleskilltext Empty Clip is an Action card available in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, it represents your player dealing 4 damage to one of your opponents. 
					.col-md-6.articlecardpanel
						img.articlehorzimg.center-block(src='../../images/de/lasersights.png')
						h4.articleskilltext Laser Sights is a Utility card also available in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, it increases your Aim score at the beginning of your turn.			

				p.articletext These two cards work quite well together. Let's walk through it. If your turn begins with a copy of Laser Sights in play, your Aim score will increase from 0 to 1. That means until end of turn, all Actions and Feats you play will get a +1  damage increase. Playing a copy of Empty Clip afterwards allows you to deal 5 damage to your opponent instead of 4. 

				img.articlevertimg(src='../../images/de/spottingtargets.png').text-left
				img.articlevertimg(src='../../images/de/trickshot.png').text-right

				p.articletext Let's look at another example.

				p.articletext First we will start the turn with a copy of Laser Sights in play, raising our Aim score to 1.

				p.articletext Next, let's play Spotting Targets.

				p.articletext Spotting Targets is an Action card available in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, you get to increase your Aim score by 2 and draw a card afterwards. Combined with the bonus received from Laser Sights, our Aim score for this turn is now 3!

				p.articletext Finally, here's Trick Shot.

				p.articletext Trick Shot is another Action card found in Deadeye's deck. Played by itself, it increases your Aim score by 1 and then deals 2 damage to any Utility. Played after Laser Sights and Spotting Targets, our Aim score raises to 4. That means that instead of dealing the 2 damage printed on the card, Trick Shot now allows you to deal 6 damage any Utility. That's a huge bonus!

				p.articletext Creating big Aim scores to deal huge amounts of damage is her biggest advantage in the game. With the Aim score reseting to 0 every turn, you'll need to find a way to sustain momentum. Still struggling to get big AIM scores? Look to Deadeye's Utility and Feats to set up sweet headshots a few turns ahead of time.
